WEBVTT

00:03.363 --> 00:07.467
Om...

00:07.468 --> 00:08.935
What the hell?

00:08.936 --> 00:11.271
- Shh! He's meditating.
- Ah.

00:11.272 --> 00:14.574
Om...

00:21.449 --> 00:25.033
I can't smoke cigars in here,
but you can make it smell

00:25.034 --> 00:26.732
like a Thai massage parlor?

00:27.801 --> 00:29.803
I would imagine.

00:29.804 --> 00:32.005
Sorry, Oscar.

00:32.006 --> 00:34.507
I know you are incensed by incense.

00:35.596 --> 00:37.077
Just trying to regain my inner peace.

00:37.078 --> 00:38.919
It's been two months
since Emily and I broke up

00:38.920 --> 00:40.423
and I'm still feeling out of balance.

00:40.424 --> 00:42.482
I did the same thing after my divorce.

00:42.483 --> 00:44.384
Only instead of meditation and chanting,

00:44.385 --> 00:46.852
it was carrot cake and Merlot.

00:47.754 --> 00:49.656
So, how was Shakespeare in the Park?

00:49.657 --> 00:51.692
Was Ralph Fiennes amazing as Henry IV?

00:51.693 --> 00:52.793
Eh.

00:52.794 --> 00:53.794
He was okay.

00:53.795 --> 00:55.018
How would you know?

00:55.019 --> 00:56.863
You fell asleep five minutes in.

00:56.864 --> 00:57.998
Oscar!

00:57.999 --> 00:59.702
How can you fall asleep
during Shakespeare?

00:59.703 --> 01:00.801
Easy.

01:00.802 --> 01:02.705
First you get confused,
then you stop listening,

01:02.706 --> 01:04.104
then, before you know it,

01:04.105 --> 01:07.139
your girlfriend's elbowing you
because Voldemort is bowing.

01:08.241 --> 01:10.777
Well, maybe you'll like
part two of the play better.

01:10.778 --> 01:11.978
The...

01:11.979 --> 01:13.547
There's a part two?

01:13.548 --> 01:15.982
Yes, remember?

01:15.983 --> 01:17.184
Thursday night.

01:17.185 --> 01:19.086
But there's a game on Thursday night.

01:19.087 --> 01:20.053
What game?

01:20.054 --> 01:21.153
Any game.

01:22.422 --> 01:23.806
Oscar!

01:23.807 --> 01:25.407
I cannot believe that
you are complaining

01:25.408 --> 01:27.539
about going to the theater with
a beautiful, cultured woman.

01:27.540 --> 01:28.929
Do you know how lucky you are?

01:28.930 --> 01:30.670
I would trade places
with you in a second.

01:32.132 --> 01:33.433
You know what?

01:33.434 --> 01:35.702
Maybe we can make that happen.

01:35.703 --> 01:38.271
Why don't you go with Charlotte?

01:38.272 --> 01:40.006
Oh, that's sweet of you, but...

01:40.007 --> 01:41.007
Oh, come on!

01:41.008 --> 01:42.008
You love artsy stuff,

01:42.009 --> 01:43.710
you hate hearing me snore,

01:43.711 --> 01:45.212
and I love not going.

01:45.213 --> 01:46.879
It's a win-win-win.

01:48.215 --> 01:51.084
Well, if Charlotte doesn't
mind, I would love to escort her.

01:51.085 --> 01:53.687
Great! What an amazing plan!

01:53.688 --> 01:57.591
Yeah, what an amazing, undiscussed plan.

01:57.592 --> 01:58.625
I'm so excited

01:58.626 --> 02:00.026
for Thursday.

02:00.027 --> 02:01.890
When we hear the immortal
words of Price Henry,

02:01.891 --> 02:04.931
"I know you all, and will awhile uphold

02:04.932 --> 02:07.567
the unyoked humor of your idleness".

02:07.568 --> 02:10.070
And I can't wait till
Thursday when I hear

02:10.071 --> 02:11.872
the immortal words of the pizza guy,

02:11.873 --> 02:14.074
"I'm here.

02:14.075 --> 02:17.209
Enjoy your cheesy bread."

