02:23.717 --> 02:24.718
Where's Felix tonight?

02:24.719 --> 02:25.719
He's out with Charlotte.

02:25.720 --> 02:26.887
In the past week,

02:26.888 --> 02:29.389
he has saved me from
a play, an art opening,

02:29.390 --> 02:32.159
and some dancing bird thing.

02:32.160 --> 02:33.994
Swan Lake?

02:33.995 --> 02:35.761
That's it.

02:36.730 --> 02:38.031
And you're not worried

02:38.032 --> 02:40.015
that Felix is gonna swoop
in and steal your woman?

02:44.305 --> 02:46.506
Well, Oscar, I'm...

02:46.507 --> 02:48.970
I'm glad you're free to hang
out now that I'm back from Japan.

02:48.971 --> 02:50.477
Why were you gone so long, Murph?

02:50.478 --> 02:51.581
Well, you know how it goes.

02:51.582 --> 02:53.814
You go on vacation, meet a girl,

02:53.815 --> 02:56.283
end up hosting a Japanese game show.

02:56.284 --> 02:58.984
You lead a dumb, crazy-ass life.

03:00.153 --> 03:01.988
You're like a hunky Forrest Gump.

03:01.989 --> 03:02.889
Oh, my God!

03:02.890 --> 03:05.826
That lady is a buyer from Macy's

03:05.827 --> 03:07.650
and she was admiring
this necklace that I made

03:07.651 --> 03:10.263
and she wants a hundred for
a big event this weekend.

03:10.264 --> 03:12.098
Oh, my God, that's great!

03:14.168 --> 03:15.368
Thank you!

03:15.369 --> 03:17.871
Opportunity is finally
knocking on my door.

03:17.872 --> 03:19.735
So, do you have all of
the hundred ready to go?

03:19.736 --> 03:22.008
No, I just have this one.

03:22.009 --> 03:25.145
That took me five hours to
make, times 99 necklaces...

03:25.146 --> 03:27.647
Oh, my God, there's
no way I can do this.

03:27.648 --> 03:29.616
Great, I just opened the door

03:29.617 --> 03:31.885
and opportunity punched me in the face.

03:31.886 --> 03:32.919
You know what?

03:32.920 --> 03:34.287
What if we help you make them?

03:34.288 --> 03:35.689
It's too crowded in our apartment,

03:35.690 --> 03:37.233
but maybe we could do an assembly line

03:37.234 --> 03:38.172
up in Oscar's place.

03:38.173 --> 03:39.226
Really?

03:39.227 --> 03:41.127
I can make it super fun for you guys.

03:41.128 --> 03:42.696
Free beer...

03:42.697 --> 03:44.364
All the onion rings you can eat.

03:44.365 --> 03:46.532
That's a lot of onion rings.

03:47.400 --> 03:48.602
This is huge.

03:48.603 --> 03:49.803
Thank you!

03:49.804 --> 03:53.607
I'm finally going to
fulfill my creative destiny!

03:53.608 --> 03:58.277
Right after I sweep up all the
dead silverfish in the pantry.

04:02.048 --> 04:04.851
Good evening, you
scrappy band of underdogs.

04:04.852 --> 04:06.186
Hey.

04:06.187 --> 04:07.954
How was the ballet?

04:07.955 --> 04:09.089
Amazing.

04:09.090 --> 04:10.257
Felix, what did you call it?

04:10.258 --> 04:11.791
An invigorating exploration

04:11.792 --> 04:13.326
of the boundaries of the human body.

04:13.327 --> 04:15.070
Well, I would like to
explore the boundaries

04:15.071 --> 04:16.228
of your human body.

04:16.230 --> 04:17.497
Ugh.

04:17.498 --> 04:19.099
I'm sorry, I knew two words in

04:19.100 --> 04:20.700
that was going south.

04:20.701 --> 04:23.270
And tomorrow night I
have secured us box seats

04:23.271 --> 04:24.771
for the Arias of Love concert,

04:24.772 --> 04:26.115
featuring our favorite soprano...

04:26.116 --> 04:28.383
Anna Netrebko!

04:29.910 --> 04:32.214
Oscar, you don't mind if I'm
out with Felix another night?

04:32.215 --> 04:35.248
Of course. I can't wait to not go.

04:35.249 --> 04:36.832
I'll change and meet you at your house.

04:36.833 --> 04:37.832
Okay.

04:41.254 --> 04:43.723
This is the life!

04:43.724 --> 04:46.793
Felix does the boring
five hours, then I swoop in

04:46.794 --> 04:49.161
