14:05.998 --> 14:08.766
"Dear Oscar, I'm so
sorry for my outburst.

14:08.767 --> 14:10.568
"I don't know what came over me.

14:10.569 --> 14:12.403
"Until further notice, I will be

14:12.404 --> 14:15.907
"at the Cleansing Breath
Zen Retreat in Connecticut.

14:15.908 --> 14:19.343
"P.S. I let the neighbors
know you'll be here alone.

14:19.344 --> 14:20.944
Don't use the stove".

14:22.947 --> 14:24.582
Oh, great.

14:24.583 --> 14:27.318
Now all I want to do is use the stove.

14:27.319 --> 14:29.620
Poor Felix.

14:29.621 --> 14:32.323
I can't help feeling a
little responsible for this.

14:32.324 --> 14:34.292
A little?

14:34.293 --> 14:36.094
Or completely?

14:36.095 --> 14:38.062
- Excuse me?
- Oh, come on!

14:38.063 --> 14:39.726
Of course he thinks
he has a crush on you.

14:39.727 --> 14:40.665
You're always like,

14:40.666 --> 14:42.369
"Felix, you know so
much about the ballet."

14:42.370 --> 14:43.401
"Felix,

14:43.402 --> 14:45.136
I got two tickets to
that thing you like."

14:45.137 --> 14:48.439
"Felix, let's get dressed
up as the Queen of England."

14:48.440 --> 14:53.177
You wanted me to ask him
so you wouldn't have to go!

14:53.178 --> 14:55.480
Well, I didn't want to go, but now I do.

14:55.481 --> 14:56.581
Who wouldn't?

14:56.582 --> 14:58.449
Look at you, with your hair

14:58.450 --> 15:01.052
and your eyes and your
intoxicating perfume?

15:01.053 --> 15:04.155
I mean, should we be
having sex right now?

15:04.156 --> 15:06.958
Really, Oscar?

15:06.959 --> 15:08.993
Your friend is obviously freaking out

15:08.994 --> 15:10.461
and you're not going after him?

15:10.462 --> 15:12.530
You are so selfish.

15:12.531 --> 15:13.531
Selfish?

15:13.532 --> 15:14.866
I brought chips!

15:14.867 --> 15:18.136
That you ate in the cab ride home.

15:18.137 --> 15:20.037
That was stress eating!

15:20.038 --> 15:22.540
And it didn't work, either,
because I'm still stressed

15:22.541 --> 15:23.708
and I'm still hungry!

15:26.944 --> 15:28.379
I'm going to make a grilled cheese.

15:28.380 --> 15:30.180
I can't use the stove!

15:34.185 --> 15:36.354
- Here's your grilled cheese.
- Ah.

15:36.355 --> 15:37.788
Have you heard from Felix?

15:37.789 --> 15:39.991
No, but it's only been one night.

15:39.992 --> 15:41.953
I don't see why everybody
is so worried about him.

15:41.954 --> 15:43.177
I mean, he's going to be fine.

15:43.178 --> 15:44.751
We're all grown-ups, right?

15:45.830 --> 15:47.999
They forgot to cut the crust off!

15:49.601 --> 15:50.668
I'll do it.

15:50.669 --> 15:51.836
Why not?

15:51.837 --> 15:53.204
I'm a career waitress.

15:53.205 --> 15:55.339
Waiting on people is what I do

15:55.340 --> 15:56.723
when I'm not failing to capitalize

15:56.724 --> 15:59.377
on life-changing opportunities.

15:59.378 --> 16:03.046
Yeah, maybe you shouldn't
be holding the knife.

16:04.715 --> 16:06.551
Aw, there she is!

16:06.552 --> 16:07.895
If those are my jewelry supplies,

16:07.896 --> 16:09.387
you can just throw them in the trash.

16:09.388 --> 16:11.756
It's 100 completed
necklaces, ready to go.

16:11.757 --> 16:13.558
We worked on them all night.

16:13.559 --> 16:15.458
All damn night.

16:16.427 --> 16:17.662
I even got a bead

16:17.663 --> 16:19.263
stuck in my ear.

16:19.264 --> 16:21.299
Yeah, yeah, it's still in there.

16:21.300 --> 16:22.960
I got to go to the hospital after this.

16:24.735 --> 16:27.738
You guys did this even
after I was such a jerk?

16:27.739 --> 16:29.707
I realized we weren't
being good friends to you.

16:29.708 --> 16:32.043
You were in a tough spot,
and you needed our help.

16:32.044 --> 16:34.544
Aww, you guys!

16:36.681 --> 16:38.049
Come on, Oscar, you too.

16:38.050 --> 16:39.617
Actually, I didn't help.

16:39.618 --> 16:42.086
It's okay, you were probably
busy dealing with Felix.

16:42.087 --> 16:43.988
Actually, I wasn't.

16:43.989 --> 16:45.423
Charlotte's right.

16:45.424 --> 16:48.059
I'm a selfish, bad, bad friend.

16:48.060 --> 16:50.060
I deserve the crusts.

16:53.898 --> 16:55.233
You guys are the best.

16:55.234 --> 16:57.335
I thought I missed my one chance.

16:57.336 --> 16:58.401
But now look.

17:05.108 --> 17:07.744
These aren't tied off.

17:07.746 --> 17:10.280
Hey, those aren't tied off!

17:12.916 --> 17:14.352
That was Oscar's job.

17:14.353 --> 17:16.953
Oh, but he wasn't there!

17:19.156 --> 17:21.125
Okay, listen up,

17:21.126 --> 17:23.388
no one is leaving here until
every one of these necklaces

17:23.390 --> 17:24.328
is finished!

17:24.329 --> 17:26.271
Uh, you remember that
thing you apologized for...

17:26.272 --> 17:27.571
Bup, bup, bup, let's go!

17:28.398 --> 17:29.867
Oh, really appreciate you guys,

17:29.868 --> 17:31.235
best friends in the whole world.

17:31.236 --> 17:32.635
Come on, move it!

17:34.138 --> 17:36.506
Hey, do I have time to
go to the E.R. first?

17:47.292 --> 17:50.727
Welcome to the Cleansing Breath
Zen Center and Yoga retreat.

17:51.796 --> 17:53.965
Yeah, okay.

17:53.966 --> 17:56.778
I'm looking for a
strange little man who...

17:56.779 --> 18:00.198
- Felix?
- Yeah.

18:00.199 --> 18:02.032
He's in the rock garden.

18:02.533 --> 18:04.200
Namaste.

18:06.404 --> 18:08.005
Felix?

18:08.006 --> 18:11.174
Are you the new janitor here?

18:12.143 --> 18:13.911
No, this is a Zen garden.

18:13.912 --> 18:15.713
By eliminating every imperfection

18:15.714 --> 18:17.315
and footprint in this place,

18:17.316 --> 18:19.217
it's possible to bring
calm to the world.

18:19.218 --> 18:20.852
Unlike some people,

18:20.853 --> 18:22.719
who seem to just be phoning it in.

18:23.988 --> 18:25.623
Okay, that's it!

18:25.624 --> 18:28.559
Oh, Lance, what happened to
your seven-day vow of silence?

18:28.560 --> 18:30.495
It's worth breaking to say that you are

18:30.496 --> 18:32.663
an insufferable,
judgmental, know-it-all

18:32.664 --> 18:35.098
who is utterly without Zen!

18:38.903 --> 18:42.373
Oh, I see someone didn't take
a vow against middle fingers.

18:42.374 --> 18:43.941
Felix, are you all right?

18:43.942 --> 18:45.243
I'm really worried about you.

18:45.244 --> 18:47.445
Well, I've been thinking about it a lot,

18:47.446 --> 18:48.913
and I guess I've decided that I...

18:48.914 --> 18:49.614
Oscar?

18:49.615 --> 18:51.482
Charlotte!

18:51.483 --> 18:52.450
What are you doing here?

18:52.451 --> 18:54.552
I was worried about Felix.

18:54.553 --> 18:56.454
What are you doing here?

18:56.455 --> 18:58.389
I was worried about Felix too.

18:58.390 --> 19:00.458
Well, at least we have
one thing in common.

19:00.459 --> 19:04.829
Hey, guys, you're really
messing up my sand pattern here.

19:04.830 --> 19:06.130
"One thing in common"?

19:06.131 --> 19:08.266
- What does that mean?
- Well, look at you.

19:08.267 --> 19:10.768
You're all beautiful
and classy and cultured,

19:10.769 --> 19:14.438
and I'm, you know, me.

19:14.439 --> 19:16.407
Yeah, so?

19:16.408 --> 19:18.943
So? What kind of a future
are we going to have

19:18.944 --> 19:21.312
if we're so different?

19:21.313 --> 19:24.582
I literally just raked that.

19:24.583 --> 19:27.084
Is that why you've been acting so weird?

19:27.085 --> 19:30.288
I don't want someone exactly like me.

19:30.289 --> 19:33.057
I love that we challenge each other.

19:33.058 --> 19:34.592
You do?

19:34.593 --> 19:37.093
Does one of you guys want to rake too?

19:38.896 --> 19:40.164
Yes.

19:40.165 --> 19:42.800
I spend all day with snooty people.

19:42.801 --> 19:45.002
I love that I get to come home to you.

19:45.003 --> 19:48.477
So you can stop pretending
to like all my artsy stuff.

19:48.478 --> 19:49.545
Thank God.

19:54.683 --> 19:56.986
Do you want to handle
this lunatic or should I?

19:56.987 --> 19:59.387
I'll start.

19:59.388 --> 20:01.856
Felix, are you okay?

20:01.857 --> 20:03.191
Yes.

20:03.192 --> 20:06.327
I suppose I'm just
ashamed for losing control

20:06.328 --> 20:08.496
and making this so
awkward for both of you.

20:08.497 --> 20:11.366
I know you think you have
feelings for me, but maybe

20:11.367 --> 20:14.436
you were just enjoying a
little female companionship.

20:14.437 --> 20:16.772
And maybe this is a sign

20:16.773 --> 20:18.540
that you're ready to move on from Emily

20:18.541 --> 20:19.874
and start dating again.

20:19.875 --> 20:21.943
I think you may be right.

20:21.944 --> 20:24.312
I just happened to be the
first woman you went out with,

20:24.313 --> 20:26.037
and you got caught up
in the fantasy of it all.

20:26.038 --> 20:26.581
Exactly, yes.

20:26.582 --> 20:27.765
This wasn't about you at all.

20:27.766 --> 20:29.718
I was just so lonely, it
could have been anyone.

20:29.719 --> 20:31.586
Well, not anyone.

20:31.587 --> 20:33.388
I mean, it could have been a mannequin.

20:33.389 --> 20:35.356
Or a broom with a wig!

20:35.357 --> 20:36.791
Or one of those

20:36.792 --> 20:37.792
inflatable...

20:37.793 --> 20:39.527
I think Felix made his point.

20:39.528 --> 20:42.964
Well, I think I'm ready to
end this self-imposed exile.

20:42.965 --> 20:44.065
Look out, Manhattan women

20:44.066 --> 20:46.468
age 35 to 55 with a
passion for Scrabble,

20:46.469 --> 20:48.803
because Felix Unger is DTF!

20:48.804 --> 20:49.571
Hmm?

20:49.572 --> 20:52.039
Determined to fornicate.

20:54.142 --> 20:55.642
Let's go.

21:05.320 --> 21:06.322
Felix!

21:06.323 --> 21:07.855
Coming!

